ake sure I avoid nested lists in the response. I'll use clear section headings and top-level bullet points instead to keep everything readable. Crafting citations succinctly is important too, like referencing ``src/backend/src/routes/notifications.ts:33-42``. \n\nWhile the instructions refer to `app/backend/src/**`, I've discovered that the actual path is within the lesson as `src/backend/src...`. It's essential I maintain accuracy while presenting this information clearly! **Mapping requirements and risks**\n\nI'm considering how the lesson surfaces in the code and want to establish clear semantics. It seems like I need to define open questions and risks with maybe four bullets each. I should make sure we clearly separate confirmed requirements from inferred choices. Perhaps I could create an explicit subsection labeled \"Confirmed Requirements\" for backend and frontend constraints, and another one for \"Inferred Hardening Choices.\" I'll draft everything carefully, ensuring that references are accurate.",
