● Summary

  Read-only inspection shows the notification-preference experience centers on
  backend route src/backend/src/routes/notifications.ts and frontend surfaces
  src/frontend/src/pages/preferences.ts,
  src/frontend/src/components/notification-toggle.ts, and
  src/frontend/src/api/client.ts.

  The hardening plan should focus on four gaps: normalize backend
  authorization semantics across all write paths, move preference-specific
  business validation out of routes and into a pure rule/service layer, make
  audit/error handling conform to the stricter project instructions, and
  upgrade the frontend from a thin toggle UI to a state-aware, accessible
  preferences experience.

  Confirmed backend constraints

  Confirmed requirements from instructions and current code:

   - Backend architecture is Route → Rule → Service, with routes limited to HTTP
  handling/delegation and rules kept pure. Global guidance also says mutating operations must be
  audited and audit must fail closed before persistence.
  .github/copilot-instructions.md:26-35,53-60,67-71
   - API-scoped guidance is the canonical backend-specific rule set for files in
  app/backend/src/**: middleware order is authenticate then authorize(role) then handler body; use
   backend status/code taxonomy; use transactions for multi-table writes; emit real-time events
  only after successful writes. .github/instructions/api.instructions.md:7-18,21-27,29-50
   - Actual notification write entry surfaces are:
   PUT /api/notifications/preferences
   PUT /api/notifications/preferences/:userId/email
   PUT /api/notifications/preferences/:userId/sms
   with GET /api/notifications/preferences/:userId as the read surface.
  src/backend/src/routes/notifications.ts:33-45,107-271
   - Notification preference writes are role-restricted and delegated sessions must not write.
  Current code confirms:
   compliance reviewers are read-only in permission matrix,
   delegated sessions are blocked in auth nuance and route logic,
   channel-specific write routes are owner-only.
  src/backend/src/rules/role-permissions.ts:7-12,22-25,48-54;
  src/backend/src/middleware/auth.ts:5-15,38-75;
  src/backend/src/routes/notifications.ts:118-145,201-228
